headline.main: LINK SEEN IN CIANO TALKS; Turkey Believed Center of Axis Concern in Mediterranean

lead_paragraph: ROME, Oct. 29 -- Count Ciano, the Italian Foreign Minister, was back in Rome today after several days of conferences with Reichsfuehrer Hitler and Joachim von Ribbentrop, the German Foreign Minister, on the Eastern Front. His trip was believed in diplomatic circles to be connected with the politico-diplomatic situation in the Mediterranean, and Turkey was mentioned as the power on which the attention of the Axis diplomatists was focused.
